Rotring Isograph & Radiograph Technical Drafting Pen Comparison
The Isograph can be dismantled completely and easily. With the Rapidograph, I was not able to dismantle the air channel (the one fused to the tip) to remove the pin that's inside. So cleaning the Rapidograph may take longer time. Overall, the Isograph is easier to maintain and refill. If you're looking for a refillable technical pen, I would recommend the Isograph over Rapidograph. You can buy the pens individually or in sets. If you're buying individually, I suggest getting a few line weights, the more popular ones being 0.3, 0.5 and 0.7. If you need more variety then 0.1 and 1.0. The thinner the line, the more maintenance is required. If the ink dries in the small pen tip, it is going to clog and be very difficult to unclog.

Keyboard shortcut to Login Window—Mac OSX
Create your own service that calls the Login Window, then assign it a keyboard shortcut. Create a Service in Automator and set "Service receives selected" to "no input" instead of "text". (Still in Automator) add 'Run AppleScript' (search on the left "apple" then double-click). In the script in place of (* Your script goes here *) you copy-paste: do shell script "'/System/Library/CoreServices/Menu Extras/User.menu/Contents/Resources/CGSession' -suspend" Save and exit. (You can name your service "Lock Screen".) Open System Preferences, Keyboard then in Keyboard Shortcuts tab and under Services you will find your service "Lock Screen" towards the bottom of the list. Now, click on "none" next to "Lock Screen" to assign ⌥⌘ L to your service. Actually I suggest rather ⌃⌥⌘ L because ⌥⌘ L is assigned in Finder.

Remove the SC Info folder If you are still unable to authorize your computer to play your purchases, you may be able to resolve your issue by removing the "SC Info" folder. To do so, follow these steps: Mac OS X Quit iTunes and any other open applications until only Finder is open. Choose Go > Go to Folder. Type /Users/Shared/SC Info and click Go. Go to folder /Users/Shared/SC Info If Finder is not already set to column view, set it by choosing View > as Columns. SC Info folder viewed in a column Select the SC Info folder and move it to the Trash by choosing File > Move to Trash. Restart the computer and open iTunes. Authorize your computer to play your purchases. Note: If you have multiple accounts you will need to authorize your computer for each account. Using Activity Monitor to read System Memory and determine how much RAM is being used
Descriptions of Free, Wired, Active and Inactive memory on a Mac. ________________________________________________ Free: This is the amount of RAM that's not being used. Wired: Information in RAM that can't be moved to the Mac's drive. The amount of Wired memory depends on the applications you are using. Active: This information is in RAM and has been recently used. Inactive: This information is in RAM but it is not actively being used, it was recently used. For example, if you've been using Mail and then quit it, the RAM that Mail was using is marked as Inactive memory. Inactive memory is available for use by another application, just like Free memory. However, if you open Mail before its Inactive memory is used by a different application, Mail will open quicker because its Inactive memory is converted to Active memory, instead of loading it from the slower drive.

Time Machine - Frequently Asked Questions 18. How can I copy my TM backups to a different location?
Your best bet is to simply start a new set of backups in the new location. Keep the old ones "on the shelf" until you're sure you don't need them. (If you're backing-up to a locally-connected disk, it's best to give it a different name.) You can always browse and restore from the old backups, via the Browse Other Time Machine Disks option (Option key + select Time Machine icon in your menubar). Some restrictions: • If your backups were made to an internal or directly-connected USB or FireWire disk or partition, you must copy all the backups for all the Macs that were backed-up to the same disk/partition that way. • You can only copy a complete set of backups, not just some individual backups. • You cannot merge two or more sets of backups, even for the same Mac. • On Leopard, you cannot change from local to network, or vice-versa. • You cannot convert case-sensitive backups to case-ignorant, or vice-versa. • You cannot copy anything from damaged/corrupted backups.

Bind variables - The key to application performance
When looking for a matching statement in the shared pool, only statements that exactly match the text of the statements are considered; so, if every SQL statement you submit is unique then you'll never get a match, and every statement you submit will need to be hard parsed. Hard parsing is very CPU intensive The way to get Oracle to reuse the execution plans for these statements is to use bind variables. Bind variables are «substituion» variables that are used in place of literals and that have the effect of sending exactly the same SQL to Oracle every time the query is executed.

Creaking front springs - Mercedes-Benz Owners' Forums
The front suspension springs of my 110K miles 220CDi C Class have started to creak and groan. Any idea what can be the cause?
rear off side squeaking - Mercedes-Benz Owners' Forums
In my limited experience this is sometimes caused by a dy and sometimes rusty contact between the top of the spring and the spring cup at the top. The dry metal rubs as the spring turns slightly as it compresses. The best lubricant for this happens to be waxoil which you can apply from a spray can through a straw or thin pipe that it comes with. Cover the brakes and squirt some around the top of the spring. Best done with the car jacked up as this allows the oil to get behind the offending contact point. It also stops the metal rusting further and hopefully solves the problem.

Explains how images that use an indexed palette store their colour data in the image file. Indexed colour images have a set palette of colours (16 colours, if 4-bit; 256 colours, if 8-bit). That pixel is rendered with the colour stored on the palette at the given index. GIFs (among other image types) are indexed colour images.
